01:17.811 --> 01:19.046
Gorgeous.

01:25.353 --> 01:28.656
Hello, Mrs. J.
Do you have any
maraschino cherries?

01:28.722 --> 01:30.458
I think so, Mister Bentley.

01:30.524 --> 01:32.526
Oh, good. You see,
Valerie's coming over
for dinner tonight,

01:32.593 --> 01:34.262
and I'm mixing
her favorite drink.

01:34.328 --> 01:36.597
I call it After Five.

01:36.664 --> 01:38.732
What's After Five?

01:38.799 --> 01:42.436
I don't know. I've never
been able to get her
to drink more than four.

01:42.503 --> 01:44.205
Oh, I say,
what a stunning dress.

01:44.272 --> 01:46.106
I'm sure Mister J
will love it.

01:46.174 --> 01:48.209
Oh, do you think
it'll fit him?

01:48.276 --> 01:50.911
Well, I suppose if he takes
the hem up a little bit.

01:50.978 --> 01:52.313
Oh, did I say that? Oh my.

01:52.380 --> 01:54.382
I'm going to ask Florence
for the cherries.

01:54.448 --> 01:57.618
Oh, Florence isn't here.
She's visiting her aunt
for a few days.

01:57.685 --> 01:59.253
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

01:59.320 --> 02:01.222
But the cherries
should be on the top shelf
in the refrigerator.

02:01.289 --> 02:02.290
Thank you.

02:05.326 --> 02:06.994
Hello.

02:07.060 --> 02:08.862
Oh, hello, Mister Wentworth.

02:08.929 --> 02:10.664
What?

02:10.731 --> 02:13.901
You want me to be in the play
at the Help Center?

02:14.802 --> 02:16.837
To replace Melinda?

02:16.904 --> 02:21.675
Oh, I couldn't.
She's a very beautiful
woman, and I...

02:23.411 --> 02:27.448
Oh, well. Thank you.

02:27.515 --> 02:31.252
Oh, well, um, how much
rehearsing time will there be?

02:31.319 --> 02:33.053
Oh, I'm sorry.

02:33.120 --> 02:37.491
But I just wouldn't feel right
leaving my husband alone
that many nights.

02:37.558 --> 02:39.993
But thank you
for asking anyway.

02:40.060 --> 02:41.061
Goodbye.

02:42.029 --> 02:43.497
What was that all about?

02:43.564 --> 02:46.700
Oh, the Help Center's putting
on a play to raise money.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.569
That was the director,
Mister Wentworth.

02:48.636 --> 02:50.070
He wanted me to play a part.

02:50.137 --> 02:51.639
Oh. What did you tell him?

02:51.705 --> 02:54.908
I said, no. I'd rather spend
my evenings with you.

02:54.975 --> 02:57.878
Of course you would.
He should have known that
in the first place.

03:00.614 --> 03:02.783
-Hello, Mister J.
-Hey, Bentley.

03:02.850 --> 03:05.519
Oh, thanks for
the cherries, Mrs. J.

03:05.586 --> 03:06.854
Hey, Bentley,
with all those cherries,

03:06.920 --> 03:08.256
you could make
a perfect gift pack.

03:08.322 --> 03:11.225
Fruits and nut. (LAUGHS)

03:11.292 --> 03:15.095
Oh, that's very good,
Mister J. A gift pack.

03:15.162 --> 03:18.299
I just hope that
Valerie has fun unwrapping me.

03:22.169 --> 03:23.371
George.

03:24.405 --> 03:25.639
Yeah, Weezy, what is it?

03:25.706 --> 03:28.008
Do you notice anything
different about me?

03:29.042 --> 03:30.511
Oh, yeah, your diet's working.

03:32.480 --> 03:35.283
George, I'm talking about
my new dress.

03:35.349 --> 03:37.851
So am I. You fit into
the dress, didn't you?
(CHUCKLES)

03:40.821 --> 03:43.591
I bought it
especially for tonight.

03:43.657 --> 03:45.359
Oh, come on, Weezy,
you ain't gotta
get all dressed up

03:45.426 --> 03:47.160
just to sit and watch me work.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.697
-What's for dinner?
-Nothing.

03:49.763 --> 03:51.031
What do you mean nothing?

03:51.098 --> 03:53.166
Well, I thought
it would be fun
if we went out tonight.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.502
Look, Weezy, I can't go out.

03:54.568 --> 03:56.370
I gotta look over
all these papers.

03:56.437 --> 03:59.507
Oh, they can wait.
Why don't we just
go out on the town?

03:59.573 --> 04:00.574
Out where?

04:00.641 --> 04:02.543
Oh, I don't know.

04:02.610 --> 04:05.279
-How 'bout a disco?
-A disco?

04:05.346 --> 04:07.981
Yeah.
Disco is where it's at today.

04:08.048 --> 04:11.118
Oh, yeah?
Well, it ain't gonna be
where I'm at tonight.

04:12.420 --> 04:13.821
Oh, come on, George,

04:13.887 --> 04:16.757
I hear
there's a great new one
called Dirty Betty's.

04:16.824 --> 04:19.460
Hmm. I'd rather
stay right here at
Filthy Florence's.

04:19.527 --> 04:20.828
(LAUGHS)

04:25.165 --> 04:28.869
George, I'm not gonna argue
about this anymore.

04:28.936 --> 04:31.739
Good, Weez, because I like
peace and quiet when I work.

04:31.805 --> 04:36.377
Well, I'm not going to be
quiet unless you take me out
to dinner and then dancing.

04:36.444 --> 04:39.613
-But, Weezy, look...
-Oh, come on, George.
It'll be healthy for you.

04:40.614 --> 04:42.149
Healthy? How?

04:42.215 --> 04:45.586
Because if you
don't take me out,
I'll break your legs.

04:51.825 --> 04:53.561
(DISCO MUSIC PLAYING)

05:18.118 --> 05:19.920
Isn't this great?

05:19.987 --> 05:22.723
Great? I think it's stupid.
(CHUCKLES)

05:22.790 --> 05:24.458
It looks like the circus
just came to town.

05:24.525 --> 05:25.759
(LAUGHS)

05:27.227 --> 05:29.229
Did you see that?

05:29.296 --> 05:31.765
-Yeah, I might be giving him
one of my business cards.
-What for?

05:31.832 --> 05:33.967
If he keeps doing that,
he's gonna have to have
his pants cleaned.

05:34.034 --> 05:35.335
(LAUGHS)

05:35.403 --> 05:37.938
Oh, George, will you stop
thinking about the business?

05:38.005 --> 05:39.973
Come on, let's get down.

05:40.040 --> 05:42.643
Oh, yeah? I'll get down,
I just hope I can
get back up again.

06:16.877 --> 06:19.312
Hey, hey, hey, Weezy,
this was a great idea.

06:19.379 --> 06:22.349
Yeah. It's almost midnight.

06:22.416 --> 06:25.118
Yeah, ain't that a drag?
We only got four more hours
before they close.

06:25.753 --> 06:27.154
Whew!

06:27.220 --> 06:29.723
But, George, shouldn't we
be leaving soon?

06:29.790 --> 06:30.858
Weezy, what are
you talking about?

06:30.924 --> 06:32.392
I didn't get
my second wind yet.

06:32.460 --> 06:33.761
But I'm tired.

06:33.827 --> 06:35.362
Hey wait, come on, Weezy,
they're gonna play now.

06:35.429 --> 06:38.098
-Oh, sorry. I'm gonna
stick this one out.
